Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the Indian innings. The players have made their way out in the middle. KL Rahul and Shubman Gill are the openers for India. Taskin Ahmed comes to bowl. Here we go.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's it, Bangladesh have been bundled out in a jiffy here. Ravichandran Ashwin loops it up and looks to bowl it full on middle but serves a low full toss that dips on the batter. Khaled Ahmed leans forward a bit and just slogs it flat toward deep mid-wicket. Jaydev Unadkat comes in and runs to his right before taking a good low catch to his wrong side as Ashwin ends with a four-fer just like Umesh Yadav. Ahmed departs for a duck and Bangladesh finish with 227/10!
Commentary.Howout: c Jaydev Unadkat b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up on a length and turning in from around off, Khaled Ahmed manages to keep it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Sharp catch from Rishabh Pant and Ravichandran Ashwin sends Mominul Haque packing with a ripper of a delivery. This is flighted on a length and outside the off stump. Mominul leans forward looking for the cover drive but opts to leave it late. The ball just angles in and bounces a bit extra as well before just flicking the gloves. Pant takes a good catch and the finger is raised. Ashwin gets his third and a fighting knock from Mominul comes to an end.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Drags it down a bit and bowls it well down leg, Rishabh Pant does well to collect it.
Floated up full and around middle, Mominul Haque pushes it toward cover.
A good bumper, over middle and leg, Taijul Islam does well to sway his head out of the way.
FOUR! Length ball on the pads, Taijul Islam tickles it fine and the ball runs away into the fence.

OUT! CAUGHT! A bit of a fumble but Mohammed Siraj hangs on to the catch. Umesh Yadav with his fourth and India are just two wickets away from bundling out Bangladesh. This is full again and outside off, inviting the shot from the batter. Taskin Ahmed goes for the expansive drive but ends up slicing it uppishly straight toward point. It is a simple chance but the ball almost pops out of Siraj's ahnd who remains cool and plays with the ball a bit before finally grabbing it.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Umesh Yadav

Commentary.Commentary: Swing and a miss! Umesh Yadav bowls this one a bit fuller and wider of the off stump, Taskin Ahmed looks to hang deep and hammer it downtown but is well beaten.
Zipping through! Length ball, slanted across the left-hander at about 142 clicks and the ball just whizzes past the outside edge.
Fullish length, angled across the left-hander, Mominul drives it off the outer half of the bat toward deep point for a run.
Flighted delivery, around middle and Taskin Ahmed keeps it out.
Quicker one, fired in full and outside off, this is stroked away to sweeper cover for a single.
Loopy delivery, full and on off, dipping on the batter, Mominul Haque does well to make the block.
Floated up, again on the pads and Mominul easily keeps it out.
On middle and leg, Mominul Haque defends it under his eye line.
Tossed up around leg stump, Mominul Haque blocks it out.
Maiden! Very full and around off, jammed out towards mid on.
Back of a length, angling in from outside off, Taskin Ahmed eases it toward point.
Goes full and looks to attack leg stump but it is just angling down leg. Taskin Ahmed makes a good leave.
Good length around off, this is tentatively pushed toward cover-point.
Shorter and outside off, nipping away a bit. Taskin Ahmed has a little dab at it but the ball beats the outside edge.
Banged in from around the wicket and over middle stump, Taskin Ahmed ducks under it well.
Slightly shorter angling it in, Taskin Ahmed tucks it to mid on for one.
Fuller length angling in, Taskin drives but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Dot.

NOT OUT! Tosses it up here with some turn, Taskin Ahmed goes for a big swing and misses. The keeper whips off the bails and the umpire goes upstairs for a stumping check. Ultra Edge shows no spike and the replay shows the foot is grounded just behind the crease.
Fuller and down leg, Taskin Ahmed looks to block it but misses and the ball hits his pads and bounces off the deck. Dot.
Goes fuller and on off, Mominul Haque knocks it to long off for one.
Flatter and on middle and leg, Mominul Haque defends it to point.
Fuller and on off, Taskin Ahmed defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Taskin Ahmed drives it to the man at covers.

OUT! LBW! On a length and on middle angling it in, Nurul Hasan looks to defend it but misses and gets a rap on the pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The keeper, Rishabh Pant urges KL Rahul to take the review and he decides to go upstairs. Fair delivery, Ultra Edge shows a flat line. Ball Tracking shows three reds and the decision is reversed. Nurul Hasan makes his way back into the hut and Bangladesh are seven down in a jiffy.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Umesh Yadav

Commentary.Commentary: Bowls it fuller and on middle, Hasan eases it to covers.
Fuller and on off angling it in, Hasan reads it well and blocks it out.
On a length and on off, Hasan taps it to short covers.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan uses the pace of the ball and guides it to third man. The fielder chases it well as the batters collect three runs.
This one lands down leg, Hasan flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan steers it to covers for none.
Goes fuller and on middle, Hasan eases it to the man at mid-wicket.
Bowls it on off again, Hasan blocks it to point.
Fuller and on off, Hasan lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Hasan punches it to covers for one.
Bowls it on off, Hasan steers it to the man at point.

A yorker right into the blockhole, Nurul Hasan flicks it to square leg for a brace. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses. A direct hit would have got the batter as shown by the replays.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mehidy Hasan makes his way back into the hut. On a length and just outside off shaping it away, Mehidy Hasan looks to cut off the back foot but gets a slight outside edge. Rishabh Pant behind the stumps makes no mistake pouching it safely to his right and Bangladesh are six down now!
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Umesh Yadav

Commentary.Commentary: Touch fuller and on off, Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, Hasan leaves it alone towards the keeper.
SIX! Tosses it up on off, Haque hangs back and lofts it over long on for a maximum. He moves to 81 now!
Bowls it on off, Haque pushes it to the man at covers.
Fuller and turning it in, Hasan looks to defend it but gets his pads. It rolls towards fine leg as the batters collect a leg bye.
Bowls it outside off, it comes in a bit. Haque looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. They collect one.
Fuller and on off, Haque defends it solidly.
On a length and on leg, Haque gently flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Good length angling it into the batter, Hasan defends it to short covers. Ends with a dot.
On a length and on off, Hasan defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Hasan eases it to short mid-wicket.
Bowls it on middle this time, Hasan defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Good shot. Fuller and on off, Hasan stands firm and caresses it past covers for a boundary! The 200 is also up for Bangladesh.
Comes 'round the wicket and bowls it on off, Hasan defends it to short covers.
Another one on off, Haque eases it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Haque eases it to covers.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter and slower too, Haque hangs back and slaps it past point for a boundary!
This one lands on off, Haque taps it to short covers.
Bowls it outside off, Haque leaves it alone.
Bowls it on off turning it away, Haque looks to defend it but misses.
On a length and on off, Hasan defends it solidly towards covers.
This one lands outside off, Hasan looks to flick it but misses. Pant makes a good stop diving to his left.
Good length angling it into the batter, Hasan fends it to point.
On a length and on off, Haque eases it to covers for a single.
Bowls it on off, this is defended off the front foot.
On a length angling it in, Haque defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan slaps it but finds the man at point. A maiden from Ashwin.
This one lands down middle, Hasan lunges and defends it solidly.
Fuller and outside leg, Hasan eases it to the man at mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan steers it to backward point. Dot.
Fuller again as this is defended towards mid on.
Fuller and on off, Hasan defends it to mid on.
On a length and on off, Hasan steers it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Hasan looks to tuck it but gets a top edge over the keeper. Pant chases it but the ball lands safely at fine leg. They collect two.
On a length and down leg, Hasan looks to defend it but gets a rap on his pads. Dot.
Bowls it on off, Haque taps it to deep covers for one.
On a length and on off, Haque defends it solidly.
Wide! A wayward bouncer on off, Haque ducks underneath it.
Fuller and on off, Haque eases it to the man at covers.
Drifted into middle and leg, Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
Keeps firing it in and bowls it flatter around off, Mehidy Hasan backs away to cut but fails to beat the man at short third man.
This is fired in fuller and into middle, Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
FOUR! Another quicker one, bowled a bit short and outside off. Mehidy Hasan rocks back and slices it through the backward point region for a boundary.
Quicker one, angled in from around off and this is punched away toward extra cover.
Flatter delivery around off, Mehidy Hasan defends it from deep inside his crease.
Digs it in a bit short and around off, extracting a bit of extra bounce. Mominul Haque awkwardly fends it away on the leg side.
Good length again, outside off this time and it is left alone for the keeper to collect.

Half an appeal for lbw but the impact seems to be outside off. Mominul Haque keeps batting outside his crease and Jaydev Unadkat angles it in on a length from around off. Mominul looks to block off the front foot but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Back of a length and on off stump, Mominul Haque gets behind the line and defends it down on the deck.
Pitches it up now and angles it into middle, Haque eases it gently toward silly mid on.
Good length around the top of off, Mominul Haque keeps it down towards cover-point.
Fires one in full and around middle, Mehidy Hasan defends it off the front foot.
Around off stump, this is blocked out.
Flighted delivery, on a length and around off, Mehidy Hasan looks to cut but the ball grips and beats the outside edge as well.
Switches to around the wicket for the right-hander and tries to slide one into the pads. Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
Drops it short now and bowls it on the pads, Mominul Haque tucks it off the back foot toward mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Starts from over the wicket and drifts it onto the off stump. Mominul Haque presses forward and solidly blocks it out.
On a length and just outside off shaping it away, Mehidy Hasan looks to defend it but misses. That was close. That will be TEA BREAK on Day 1.
On a length angling it in from outside off, Mehidy Hasan reads it well and lets it go.
Good length shaping it away, Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan knocks it back towards the bowler who stops it well. Dot.
On a length and on leg, Mehidy Hasan gently flicks it to the man at square leg.
Slightly shorter and outside leg, Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Maiden! Flatter one outside off, this is kept out off the back foot and toward cover.
Shorter and down the leg side, Mominul Haque goes on the back foot before letting it through to the keeper.
Flatter one, angled into the stumps, this is defended off the back foot.
This is fuller and around off stump, Haque blocks it out yet again.
Slides one in from around off, Mominul Haque blocks it out.
Flatter one on off stump, this is flicked away to mid-wicket.
Drifted in from around off, Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
Pushed through quicker on off stump, Mehidy Hasan nudges it onto the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, this is pushed toward mid on.
Flighted delivery on the pads, Mominul Haque works it behind square on the leg side for one.
Floated up full and on middle, this is pushed away toward wide mid on.
Nicely bowled! Looped up on off stump, drawing the batter forward, Mominul Haque looks to block but the ball turns away and takes the outside edge before falling short of the man at first slip.
Nagging length around off and turning away a bit. Mehidy Hasan gets squared up but manages to block it out.
Full again and around off, Mehidy Hasan drives it straight to Jaydev Unadkat at extra cover and he fumbles a bit. The batters don't go for the single though.
This is full and on off stump, it is defended off the front foot.
Nicely drifted onto middle, Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
Flighted, around off and kept out on the off side.
A bit dragged down and angled into the pads, Mehidy Hasan defends it out.
Floated up around off stump, Mominul Haque strokes it toward cover.
Flatter one, angling in from off stump, Haque blocks it off the back foot.
Around middle, this is kept out on the off side.

A bit of excitement again in the Indian camp for an lbw appeal but it is turned down. This is the carrom ball, angled into the pads. Mominul Haque looks to block but misses. The ball hits the pads and India opt against the review this time around.
Fired in on off stump, this is pushed out on the off side.
FOUR! Up and over! Tosses it up outside off, Mominul Haque dances down the track and lofts it over extra cover for a boundary.
On off, kept out on the off side.
Flighted delivery around middle, Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
Drags it down now and bowls it around leg stump, Mominul Haque goes back in his crease and works it past square leg for a single.
Floats it up a bit now around off and this is pushed away onto the off side.
Flatter one, angled into middle and Haque keeps it out off the back foot.
Axar Patel comes from over the wicket and fires it in around off stump, Mominul Haque blocks it out.
Floated up outside off, driven through the cover region for a single.

Poor review in the end from India. Floated up on a shorter length and around leg stump. This one turns away from the left-hander as well. Mominul Haque goes on the back foot and looks to work it leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. Ravichandran Ashwin seems excited and thinks he has got his man but the umpire disagrees. Rishabh Pant from behind the stumps says that they can take a chance and it is reviewed. Nothing on UltraEdge but Ball Tracking shows that it is pitching outside leg and the review is lost.
Gives it a nice loop and bowls it around off, Haque watches it closely and lets it through.
Tossed up on off stump, Mominul Haque stays solid in defense.
Flights it up a bit and around off, Haque edges it down with soft hands past first slip.
Comes from around the wicket and pushes it through on off stump, Mominul Haque blocks it out.
FOUR! This one lands down leg, Mehidy Hasan uses the pace of the ball and helps it through fine leg for a boundary!
Goes fuller and on off, Mominul Haque sweeps it to backward square leg for one.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Mominul Haque eases it to square leg. Dot.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Fuller and on off, Mominul Haque flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, Mominul Haque lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on middle, Mehidy Hasan lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN! Ravichandran Ashwin gets the big fish here. Tosses it up on middle, slower through the air. Litton Das looks to come down the track and flick it away but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and lobs towards KL Rahul at short mid-wicket. The skipper takes a dolly and Litton Das departs for 25.
Commentary.Howout: c KL Rahul b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Flatter one with some turn, Litton Das lunges and blocks it away.
Another one on off, Mominul Haque guides it to backward point. The misfield allows the batters to steal one run.
Bowls it on off again, Mominul Haque lunges and defends it away.
Goes fuller and on off, Mominul Haque defends it solidly.
On a length and on off, Litton Das cuts it but finds the fielder at backward point.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Litton Das hangs back and guides it through backward point for a boundary. Good shot!
Good-length delivery outside the off. Das covers the off stumpand lets it go.
On off, blocked out.
Around the wicket. Good-length delivery on the off stump. Das punches it down to covers for one.
Fuller and on off, Mominul Haque defends it solidly.

Bowls it on a length and just outside off, it nips in a bit. Litton Das looks to block it but the ball gaps between his bat and the pads, it brushes his pads and lobs towards the keeper. Mohammed Siraj thought it was an inside edge and appeals but the umpire is unmoved. That was close!
SIX! In the air and all the way. Shorter and on off, Das rocks back and pulls it over square leg for a maximum!
FOUR! Excellent timing on this. Slightly shorter and on off, Das hangs back and punches it past covers for a boundary!
Slightly shorter and on off, Das pulls it towards deep square leg for a brace. Good fielding by Jaydev Unadkat in the deep.
On a length angling it in from outside off, Das reads it well and makes a tight leave.
On a length angling it in, Das blocks it to covers.
This one lands on middle, Haque eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards covers.
This one lands outside off, Das guides it to deep point and collect three runs off it. Good running!
Bowls it on off, Haque eases it to covers for one.
Flatter and on off, Das eases it to the man at square leg and scampers for a single.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards the man at short leg.
Good piece of timing here. Fuller and on off, Das opens the face of his bat and guides it to deep covers. The fielder chases it as the batters collect three runs.
Bowls it on leg this time, Haque clips it to square leg for one.
Goes fuller this time and on off, Haque defends it solidly.
FOUR! On a length and outside off, Haque looks to slap it but gets a top edge through third man for a boundary!
Good length again, on off. Haque eases it to the man at point.
On a length and on off shaping it in, Haque lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it on off, Das lunges and defends it to short covers.
Another dot ball as this is again defended towards Axar Patel.
Goes fuller and on off, Patel defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
This one lands on leg, Das nudges it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Bowls it outside off, Das leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, this is defended back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Slightly shorter and outside off, Haque uses the pace of the ball and helps it through backward point for a boundary! And, that will be FIFTY for Mominul Haque on his return to the side, a much-needed inning for him and for his team as well.
Fuller and on off, Haque defends it solidly.
FOUR! Good shot. Bowls it shorter and outside off, Haque uses the pace of the ball and plays an upper cut through third man for a boundary!
On a length and on the channel outside off, Haque leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, this one nips in a bit. Haque reads it well and blocks it out.
On a length and outside off, Haque eases it back towards the bowler.
Another dot ball as this is again defended towards the cover region.
Flatter and on off, Haque defends it to covers.
Bowls it just outside off, Haque let's it through towards the keeper.
This one lands on off, Haque defends it to the man at silly point.
Goes fuller again, Haque nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on off, Haque defends it solidly towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That's a jaffa from Jaydev Unadkat! On a length and just outside off, angling in as well. The ball shapes away from the batter though after pitching, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to defend it but misses and gets a slight outside edge. The ball carries behind and Rishabh Pant makes no mistake. Bangladesh lose their fourth wicket!
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jaydev Unadkat

Commentary.Commentary: Bowls it on off, this one nips in a bit. Rahim defends it solidly.
On a length angling it in, Rahim defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Haque looks to flick it but miscues it to backward point. It carries and just falls short of the fielder. Unadkat is getting closer here.
Another one outside off shaping it in, Haque makes another tight leave.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, this one nips in a touch. Haque reads it well and makes a tight leave.
Nagging length, angling it in from around off, Mushfiqur Rahim leans forward to defend.
Around off again and it is kept out well.
Angling it into the off pole, Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter delivery around off, kept out by Rahim.
Drifts it onto middle and leg, Rahim nudges it gently onto the leg side.
FOUR! Starts off with a real loosener, full and down the leg side. Mushfiqur Rahim gets inside the line of the ball and sweeps it into the fine leg fence.

Edged but safe! Good length around the fifth stump line, Mominul Haque pushes at it and gets an outside edge that goes to the left of the man at fourth slip. The fielder does get a hand on it and the batters pick up a couple of runs.
Length again, in that channel around off and Mominul Haque shoulders arms at it.
Good length outside off, left alone by the batter.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Pitched up again by Unadkat, trying to attack the middle stump. Mominul Haque forces the drive through mid-wicket and mid on and the ball trickles away into the fence.
FOUR! Mominul Haque joins the party now and these two getting a real move on here. Full and on middle, Haque clips it well in front of the square on the leg side to find the fence.
Pitched up around the off stump, Mominul Haque stays solid in defense.
FOUR! A hat-trick of boundaries now for Mushfiqur Rahim and Ravichandran Ashwin seems a bit out of sorts. Drops it short and wide, Rahim rocks back and cuts it past point for a boundary.
FOUR! Lovely shot once again from Mushfiqur Rahim. Tossed up full and on the legs, Rahim gets to the pitch of the ball and drills it back past the bowler for another boundary.
FOUR! Short and around off, turning in. Mushfiqur Rahim goes deep in his crease and makes a bit of room before slapping it away into the cover boundary.
Quicker one, down leg, this is swept away down to fine leg for a run.
On a length around middle and leg, Mominul Haque keeps it out with ease.
Flatter delivery, a bit shorter around off and staying low. Mushfiqur Rahim rocks back and pushes it out towards cover for a single.
A touch fuller and around leg stump, nudged away toward mid-wicket for a single.

Jaydev Unadkat comes around the wicket now to the right-hander and angles it into the pads. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to block but misses and gets hit high on the pads. There is a bit of an appeal for lbw but KL Rahul doesn't review. Seemed a bit high.
Good length around leg stump, Rahim looks to tuck it away but gets it off the thigh pads toward square leg.
Pitched up on off stump, Rahim taps it onto the off side.
Well bowled! On a hard length, tighter line around off and angling across the batter. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to get behind the line but is beaten.
Jaydev Unadkat comes back in for his second spell and starts off with a fuller delivery on off stump. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it off the front foot.
Shortens the length and looks to turn it into the pads, Mushfiqur Rahim goes on the back foot and nudges it down through leg slip for a single. The 100 is now up for Bangladesh.
Tosses it up now on middle, Mushfiqur Rahim leans forward and flicks it toward mid-wicket.
Drifted onto the pads, this is nudged away to short leg.
Flighted around off, Mushfiqur Rahim uses his feet to make the block.
Floats it up now, full and around off, Rahim blocks it out.
Nicely bowled! Tossed up on a length and around off. Ashwin is able to get sharp turn and bounce as Mushfiqur Rahim is left bamboozled.
Dragged down around the pads, this is tucked away wide of the man at fine leg for a couple of runs.
Goes full and wide now, Mominul Haque gets tempted into the cover drive but the ball is angled in and takes the inside edge before hitting the pads.
Shortish length, angling in from around off, this is kept down toward mid on.
Back of a length and around off stump, Mominul Haque gets behind the line and keeps it down on the off side.
Good length around the top of off, Mominul Haque taps it toward backward point.
Full and angling into middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
Fullish length on the fifth stump line, left alone for the keeper to collect.
Just pitches it a bit further up and keeps it outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim shoulders arms at it.
Good length again and outside off, Rahim once again puts a stride across but is able to nudge it down toward the gully region.
Hard length around middle, tucked away toward mid-wicket.

Mohammed Siraj slants this in on a length and tries to attack the off stump. Mushfiqur Rahim puts a big stride across as he looks to block but misses. There is a huge appeal from the bowler for lbw but the keeper isn't sure. KL Rahul does review it at the last moment. UltraEdge comes up first and indicates that it is pad first. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is outside off and India lose a review.
Bowled from a bit wider of the crease and angling into off stump, Mushfiqur Rahim solidly keeps it out.

FOUR! Around the top of off and at 140 clicks. Mominul Haque stays back and just uses the pace of the ball to edge it past backward point. Ravichandran Ashwin chases it down and gets to it but fumbles and the ball ends up in the ropes.
Bowls it a bit fuller and wider of the off stump, Mominul Haque is content to shoulders his arms at it.
Banged in of a hard length and around off, Haque leaves it alone and the ball angles in a long way after passing the stumps.
Beaten! Umesh Yadav comes from around the wicket to the left-hander and angles it in on a length. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge.
Fullish length on off stump, Haque taps it toward cover-point.
Length ball, angled into the pads and this is flicked away down to fine leg for a single.
Switches to around the wicket now and bowls it full on middle, Mominul Haque makes a solid block on the off side.
This is pitched up on off stump, Mominul Haque blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length angling into middle, Mushfiqur Rahim tucks it past square leg for an easy single.
Goes full and bowls it around the fifth stump line, Rahim looks to play at it but lets it through to the keeper in the end.
Good length, slanting it in from around off stump, Mushfiqur Rahim gets behind the line of the ball and defends it out.
Pitched up around off and angling in, Mushfiqur Rahim goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Good length, well outside off and left alone by the batter.
Stayed low! Banged in short and over off stump, Mominul Haque looks to duck under it but the ball doesn't rise up much and flicks the helmet on its way to the keeper.
A bit of aggression from the bowler. Umesh Yadav bowls it full and on off, Mominul Haque drives it back to him and Umesh just acts to throw it back to the batter.
Serves it a bit full and around off, Mominul Haque nudges it down to point.
Length again and in line with the stumps, Mominul Haque blocks it out.
Nicely bowled! Pitched up in that channel around off and angling it away, Mominul Haque has a dab at it at the last moment but gets beaten past the outside edge.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bowls it fuller and down leg, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
Fuller again, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it to the gully region.
FOUR! Excellent placement on this. Bowls it fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim creams it past covers for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it to covers. A slight mix up but the batters decide not to take a single.
Drags his length back a bit and bowls it outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim shoulders arms at it.
On a length angling it into the batter, Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it back towards Mohammed Siraj.
Good length with some extra bounce, pace off. Mominul Haque fends it to covers.
Fuller one and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to deep backward square leg for one.
Good length and on off, 133 kph. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it to square leg.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim taps it to the man at covers.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it to short covers.

OUT! TAKEN! Umesh Yadav strikes right after the break. Bowls it on a length and on off, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play the lofted drive but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and carries towards mid off. It lobs up towards Cheteshwar Pujara and he takes a dolly. The Bangladesh skipper departs!
Commentary.Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Umesh Yadav

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller and on off, Mominul Haque lunges and defends it out solidly. That will be LUNCH for Day 1.
Fuller and down leg again, Mominul Haque looks to sweep but misses and Pant again fails to grab it. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters collect two byes.

Bowls it down leg following the batter, Shakib Al Hasan moves forward to play at it but misses. Rishabh Pant misses it as well as the ball rolls towards fine leg, they cross for a bye. There was a chance for a stumping.
Fuller and on middle, Shakib Al Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Shakib Al Hasan covers his line and blocks it away.
Fuller and on leg, Shakib Al Hasan moves forward and blocks it to covers.
Bowls it on off with some turn, Mominul Haque lunges and defends it away.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Mominul Haque just flicks it using his wrists through square leg for a boundary!
This one lands down leg, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to square leg for one.
Flatter and on off, Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to the man at mid on.
Fuller again, on off. Shakib Al Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan eases it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it outside off turning it away, Mominul Haque lets it go.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended off the front foot.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Mominul Haque gets on his knee and drives it past covers for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one, Mominul Haque defends it to mid on.
Flatter and on leg, Mominul Haque defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length in the channel outside off, Shakib Al Hasan lets it through towards the keeper.
Short ball on off, Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone.
Outside off again, Shakib Al Hasan looks to cut it but misses again.
Bowls it outside off, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller delivery angled into the off stump. Mominul Haque looks to drive on the front foot but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. They collect one.
Fuller and on off, Mominul Haque defends it to the man at mid-wicket.

Bowls it outside off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to mid off. Mominul Haque runs for one but Shakib Al Hasan sends him back. The fielder has a shy at the non strikers end. Replay shows that the batter was well in. Close!
Length delivery outside the off stump. Played towards the cover region.
Slightly shorter one with a hint of turn, Mominul Haque looks to cut it but gets an outside edge as the ball carries and lands safely at fine leg. The batters collect three runs.
Goes outside off, Mominul Haque defends it towards covers.
Fuller again, Mominul Haque taps it to extra cover for none.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to mid off for a quick single.
Good length shaping it away, Mominul Haque taps it to the man at covers.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket and scampers through for a single.
Good length outside off and angled across, Shakib leaves it covering his off stump.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly off the front foot.
On a length and down leg, Mominul Haque looks to flick it but gets his pads. Rishabh Pant dives it to his right and manages to gets his hand on it. They cross for a leg bye.
On a length and on middle, Haque eases it to the man at square leg.
SIX! Up and over. Fuller and on off, Shakib dances down the track and heaves it over the cow corner fence for a maximum!
This one lands on off, Shakib defends it solidly.
Bowls it wide outside off, Shakib leaves it alone.
FOUR! Goes on the charge. Fuller and outside off, Shakib shimmies down the wicket and drills it past extra covers for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Shakib blocks it back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on leg, Shakib moves forward and defends it away.
Outside off, left alone.
Bowls it in the channel outside off, Mominul Haque shoulders arms at it.
Another one on off with some extra bounce. Mominul Haque fends it to point.
Good length, on off. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to extra covers for one.
Slightly shorter one outside off, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length angling it in, some extra bounce as well. Shakib Al Hasan fends it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up around middle, this is solidly defended off the front foot.
Floated up, full and on middle and leg, Mominul Haque keeps it out.
Around middle and leg, kept out on the leg side.
Drifted onto middle and leg, Shakib Al Hasan gets an inside edge past leg slip and picks up a single.
Nicely flighted, on off stump and this is eased away toward cover.
Tossed up around middle, Shakib Al Hasan steps down the track but gets a bit beaten in the flight. Shakib ends up pushing it toward mid off.
Good length, cutting in from around off, Mominul Haque keeps it out.
Length ball, a bit outside off and Haque leaves it alone.
FOUR! Too full and straight, Mominul Haque clips it away through square leg and picks up a boundary. He gets into double-figures now, the first time after 9 innings. The 50 is also up for Bangladesh.
Good length outside off, left alone for the keeper to collect.
This is a bit fuller and angles in sharply, Shakib Al Hasan looks to come forward but gets turned inside-out. Shakib manages to edge it past point and picks up a single.
Swing and a miss! Length ball, outside off, Shakib Al Hasan looks to thrash it through covers but gets beaten on the inside edge.
MISFIELD AND FOUR! Tossed up, full and outside off, Mominul Haque drives it sweetly toward cover where the fielder lets it through and the ball runs away into the fence.
Flatter delivery, attacking the stumps, Mominul Haque blocks it out.
Flatter one around off, Haque keeps it out.
Flighted delivery around off, the ball grips and bounces a bit extra as well, Mominul Haque plays inside the line.
Pushed through quicker and around the pads, Haque nudges it past leg slip.
Nagging length, on off stump and going on with the arm. Mominul Haque goes deep in his crease to keep it out.
Fullish length, on the fifth stump line and Shakib has a little dab at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, in that channel around off, Shakib Al Hasan bats well outside his crease to negate the bounce but is beaten past the outside edge.
Goes full and angles it into off stump, Mominul Haque clips it away through mid-wicket and picks up three runs.
Half an appeal but angling down leg it seems. On a good length yet again and angling into the pads, Mominul Haque looks to block but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good length on off stump, Mominul Haque defends it out on the off side.
This is dug in short and around off stump, Mominul Haque lets it through to the keeper.
A wicket-maiden! This is nicely flighted and on middle and leg, Shakib Al Hasan keeps it out.
Floated up around the pads, Shakib looks to block but gets an inside edge on it.
Slows it up now and drifts it into middle and leg, Shakib Al Hasan makes yet another block.
Flatter one around middle, Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Najmul Hossain Shanto takes the risk of padding the ball away and ends up paying the ultimate price. Ashwin bowls this one on a length and looks to slide it in from around off. Shanto gets a big stride across and just pads it away. There is a huge appeal for lbw once again by Ravichandran Ashwin and this time he gets his man. Najmul Hossain Shanto does review it and as he offered no shot, the third umpire goes straight to Ball Tracking. Ball Tracking shows the wickets as umpire's call and all of a sudden Bangladesh have lost both their openers.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, full and around off stump, Najmul Hossain Shanto edges it down towards the gully region.
Good length, in that channel around off, Mominul Haque looks to play at it but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! A maiden Test wicket for Jaydev Unadkat and Bangladesh lose their first! Unadkat just keeps on bowling it on a good length and around off. He extracts that extra bounce once again and Zakir Hasan is caught on the crease. Hasan looks to awkwardly fend it off the back foot but the ball takes the gloves and pops up around gully where KL Rahul takes a simple catch. Unadkat is absolutely elated and rightly so.
Commentary.Howout: c KL Rahul b Jaydev Unadkat

Commentary.Commentary: Length ball around middle, just nudged away gently in front of mid-wicket for a quick single.

Another huge appeal for lbw but it is turned down yet again. Fullish length and angling into middle and leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to flick but misses and the ball thuds into the pads. The bowler seems interested but they opt against the review. Might have been missing leg.
Around the top of off, blocked out on the off side.
Ouch! Jaydev Unadkat serves this one on a good length around off and the ball just takes off. Najmul Hossain Shanto is on the front foot but gets taken aback and gets hit on the gloves.
Tossed up again but outside off and the ball turns away a fair bit, left alone by Hasan.
Tossed up on off stump, Zakir Hasan defends it with the turn toward cover.
Floated up around middle, Shanto works it in front of mid-wicket for a single.
On off stump, this is punched back to the bowler.

Ravichandran Ashwin tosses it up a bit on leg stump, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to block off the front foot but misses and gets hit on the pads. Ashwin seems excited but the umpire turns it down. No review is taken and rightly so as the replays show that it was going down leg.
Quicker one, a bit fuller and skidding in from outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto makes a good leave.
Good length, angling into middle and leg, Shanto tucks it toward square leg for one.
FOUR! Sweetly timed by Najmul Hossain Shanto. Overpitched around middle, Shanto with a gentle push and the ball runs away to the right of mid on and into the fence.
Shortens the length now and bowls it over off stump, Shanto gets behind the line to block.
A tad fuller and angling into the off stump, Najmul Hossain Shanto solidly blocks it off the front foot.
And again! Good length, close to the off stump and zipping past the outside edge.
Beautifully bowled. This is pitched a bit further up and in that channel around off. The ball angles in but shapes away from the left-hander as Najmul Hossain Shanto is beaten past the outside edge.
Pulls back the length a bit and bowls it around off, Zakir Hasan looks to block but is well beaten outside the off stump.

Tossed up, a bit fuller and around off, turning away as well. Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes at it with hard hands and gets an outside edge past the slip cordon. The ball trickles toward third man as the batters come back for the third with ease.
Floats it up now around the pads, Najmul Hossain Shanto works it 'round the corner and picks up a couple of runs.
Drifted onto the pads, Zakir Hasan brooms it down to deep backward square leg for a single.
Flighted this time, on off stump, Hasan defends it on the off side.
Starts off with a ripper! This is served on a nagging length and around off stump. The ball bounces and turns away sharply as well and Zakir Hasan is left bamboozled.
Length ball, around the fifth stump line, left alone for the keeper to collect.

Uppish but safe! This is pitched up around off, Zakir Hasan looks to play it leg side but closes the face of the bat early. The ball goes off the leading edge and flies past the fielder at point. The fielder chases it down as the batters come back for the third.
Lovely line from Unadkat. Good length, tighter around the off stump and just holding its line. Zakir Hasan plays inside the line of the ball.
Goes full and outside off, Zakir Hasan shoulders arms at it.
On a good length and angling into middle and leg, Zakir Hasan looks to flick but fails to get it away.
Good running! Pitched up around off, Najmul Hossain Shanto presses forward and pushes it out toward cover for a quick single.
Slightly shorter and down leg, Zakir Hasan ducks underneath it.
Slightly shorter and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto pulls it to square leg for one.
On a length shaping it into the batter, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it back towards the bowler.
Some extra bounce angling in from outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto reads it well and lets it go.
On off this time, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends this one back towards the bowler.
Shorter one on leg, Shanto ducks underneath it.
Bowls it on off, Hasan defends it solidly.
On a length and on off, slower too. Shanto looks to flick it but gets a leading edge. It carries and lands safely between the fielders at mid on. They collect one. Close!
Angles it in from outside off, Shanto watchfully blocks it away.
Another one with some extra bounce, Shanto fends it to mid-wicket.
Length ball with some extra bounce, Shanto defends it to mid off.
On a length angling it into the batter, Shanto reads it well and blocks it to square leg.
Good length angling it in, Shanto works it to mid-wicket for a single.
This one lands on off, Shanto eases it to covers.
Another fuller one, Shanto flicks it but finds the man at backward square leg.
Fuller again and on off, Shanto defends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it full and on off, Shanto taps it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Hasan flicks it to backward square leg for one.
FOUR! Good shot. Fuller and outside off shaping it away, Shanto uses the pace of the ball and guides it past backward point for a boundary!
Length ball angling it away, Shanto fends it to the man at point.
Full and outside off, Shanto looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards slips. Dot.
Fuller and outside off, Shanto defends it to the man at mid off.
Good length with some extra bounce, Shanto defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
On a length and just outside off angling it away, Shanto looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A maiden from Yadav. Slightly shorter one, Hasan looks to pull it but misses as the ball hits his ribs and bounces off the deck.
On a length and on middle, Hasan covers his line and blocks it away.
Bowls it just outside off shaping it away a bit, Hasan looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge again!
Fuller and on off, Hasan defends it solidly towards mid off.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Hasan let's it through towards the keeper.
Fuller and on off, Hasan knocks it straight to the man at mid on.
On a length and down leg, Hasan works it to backward square leg for one.
Good length angling it in, on middle and leg. Hasan fends it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Bowls it on middle and leg, fuller in length. Hasan looks to flick it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence. Lucky boundary!
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Hasan looks to block it but misses.
Good length and on leg, Hasan flicks it to the man at square leg.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan leaves it alone.
This one lands outside off shaping it away, Shanto looks to defend it but gets completely squared up and misses.
Another fuller delivery as this is defended back towards the bowler. Good bowling from Yadav here.
Goes fuller and on middle, Shanto blocks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Similar to the last delivery, Shanto looks to defend it but misses again!
Bowls it just outside off with some extra bounce, shaping it away. Shanto looks to defend it but misses. Close!
On a length and outside off shaping it away, Hasan looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. They cross.
Bowls it full and on off, Shanto defends it to mid on.
Fuller one and on off, Shanto covers his line and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Good length with some extra bounce, Hasan taps it to covers for a single.
Fuller one this time, on leg. Hasan reads it well and eases it to mid-wicket.
Another one outside off as Hasan leaves it alone towards the keeper again.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, Hasan leaves it alone.
This one lands outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it to short covers. Ends his over with a dot ball.
Good length with some extra bouce, Najmul Hossain Shanto covers his line and blocks it towards short mid-wicket.
Bowls it fuller and just outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it to the man at mid-wicket. Dot.
Bowls it on leg this time, Zakir Hasan gently flicks it to backward square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Zakir Hasan defends it towards the man at mid off.

Dropped! A chance gone abegging. Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan shuffles across and looks to flick it but mistimes it completely. The ball carries towards deep backward square leg. Mohammed Siraj runs to his right to take it and makes a diving attempt but just manages to get his hands on it. Close! The batters get a couple of runs as well.
Good length shaping it away, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto lets it go.
FOUR! Fine shot. Goes fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets on his knee and drills it straight down the ground for a boundary! Shanto and Bangladesh are away now.
On a length and on leg with some extra bounce, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to block it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Good length and just outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it solidly to mid off.
Another one shaping it away, this was a tad wider. Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves this alone as well.
Starts with a good-length delivery in the channel shaping it away, Najmul Hossain Shanto shoulders arms at it.

India are still without their regular skipper Rohit Sharma but KL Rahul has led the team well in his absence. The return to form for Cheteshwar Pujara is a big plus for them and almost everyone from the top order to the tailenders contributed with the bat in the 1st Test. Kuldeep Yadav grabbed his opportunity with both hands and the overall bowling looks in fine form as well. So, which side will make early inroads on Day 1? We shall find out. Toss and team news in a bit.

Bangladesh lost by a huge margin in the 1st Test but that could have been even worse given how they batted in the first innings. They did have a much better outing with the bat second time around and they will be looking to improve further. As for their bowling, it was good but they need to be a bit more lethal if they are to get the win here. The likes of Taijul Islam and Mehidy Hasan will be key for them and with skipper Shakib Al Hasan fit to bowl again, that will certainly be an added advantage for the hosts.

Hello and a warm welcome ladies and gentlemen to Day 1 of the 2nd and final Test match between Bangladesh and India at the Sher-e-Bangla Stadium in Mirpur. The hosts are 1-0 down and will have to win here in order to end the series on level terms. As for India, they will be hoping for more of the same and get that 2nd win to solidify their position on the World Test Championship table.
... DAY 1, SESSION 1 ...

India's tour of Bangladesh is coming to an end and in the 2nd and final Test match, the caravan moves back to the Shere-e-Bangla Stadium in Mirpur. It was an eventful first Test match with India winning by a big margin in the end. Bangladesh were poor with the bat in the first innings but having had to chase more than 500 runs, the hosts showed a lot of grit and determination to take the game into the final day. The debutant Zakir Hasan was the star of the hosts' batting with a century in the fourth innings but they will need a lot more from their more experienced batters. India, on the other hand, will be quite content with their showing as Kuldeep Yadav weaved his magic with the ball in both innings and Cheteshwar Pujara too made a century that will serve as a confidence booster. With the visitors now in a good position to qualify for the World Test Championship final, they will look to ascertain their claim even further. The hosts though will take a lot of confidence from their performance in the fourth innings and will look to pull off an upset here. While the pitch in Chattogram kept on getting better for the batters, it most likely won't be the same case in Mirpur as the bowlers will get a lot more help. So, how will this tour end? Will India sweep away the Test series? Or will Bangladesh level it at 1-1? We shall find out over the course of the best few days.

We are back for Bangladesh's second innings and there are 9 overs remaining in the day, light permitting that is. The umpires and the players are out in the middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto and Zakir Hasan are the openers for Bangladesh. It will be Umesh Yadav who will get proceedings underway with the ball here.
... THIRD INNINGS ...

India will be disappointed with their performance as they couldn't reach the 400-run mark which looked possible at the end of the second session. The Pant-Iyer partnership was the key one for India but unfortunately, neither batter could not score a century. Pant scored 93 whilst Iyer scored 87. Nonetheless, they have a lead of 87 runs and will hope to bundle their opponents to a low total. Can India take some quick wickets now? Or will Bangladesh walk out of Day 2 at no loss? We shall find out shortly...

A good comeback after the damage done in the second session and Shakib Al Hasan will be happy with the team's performance. They got Rishabh Pant early on at the start of the final session and Shreyas Iyer soon followed the suit. Once the set batters lost their way, the wickets kept on tumbling for India. Shakib Al Hasan was the pick of the bowlers in the final session as he bagged 4 wickets. The onus is now on their batters to put up a solid opening stand and stay wicketless at the end of Day 2.

OUT! STUMPED! That's it Shakib Al Hasan picks up his fourth wicket and India are bowled out late on Day 2. Mohammed Siraj pre-meditates and shimmies down the track. Shakib holds it back and pushes it wider of the off pole. Siraj throws the kitchen sink at it but gets beaten in the flight and the ball keeps a bit low as well. Nurul Hasan whips off the bails and Siraj seems very disappointed. India finish with 314 runs on the board and lead by 87 runs.
Commentary.Howout: st Nurul Hasan b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Tossed up on a length and around off, Siraj plays the sweep against the turn and hits it uppishly to the left of the man at square leg for a boundary.
Floats this one up, full and on leg stump, Mohammed Siraj keeps it out off the front foot.
Quicker one, around middle, this one stays low and skids on as well. Jaydev Unadkat manages to keep it out on the off side.
This is tossed up on middle and leg, Mohammed Siraj dances down the track and looks for the heave leg side but completely miscues it down to long off for a single.
Beaten! Nicely flighted around off and turning away, Siraj looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Tossed up on middle, Mohammed Siraj advances and whips it helicopter-style towards mid-wicket.
Holds it back a touch and drifts it onto middle and leg, Siraj makes another block off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, dipping on the batter and Siraj blocks it out.
Leg bye! Shorter and down leg, Siraj looks to tuck it away but the ball deflects off the pads and goes towards fine leg. They get a leg bye.
Flighted, around middle, Siraj makes yet another good block.
Looped up, full and on middle, Mohammed Siraj lunges forward and keeps it out.
Nicely drifted onto the leg stump, Siraj prods and blocks it out.
Pulls back the length and bowls it around middle, Jaydev Unadkat works it leg side for a single.
Flighted delivery around off, Unadkat keeps it out.
This is drifted down the leg side, Siraj waits for it and just nudges it fine past the diving fielder at leg slip for a couple of runs.
Flatter one on middle, Siraj is able to block it out.
Slows it up a touch and bowls it around off, Mohammed Siraj leans forward to block.
Mohammed Siraj walks in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Umesh Yadav's quickfire inning comes to an end and India now lead by 78 runs. Taijul Islam tosses this one up on a length and outside the off stump. The ball is turning away and Yadav looks for the big heave across the line. The ball takes the toe end of the bat and goes toward the first slip where Litton Das takes a comfortable catch around his face. Taijul is now one wicket away from a five-fer.
Commentary.Howout: c Litton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary.Commentary: Flighted delivery, on off stump and blocked off the front foot by Yadav.
FOUR! Taijul Islam comes into the attack and starts off with a quicker one down leg. Umesh Yadav just tickles it into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Floated up full and at the stumps, Umesh Yadav knocks it down to long on for a single.
This is sliding in from off stump, Yadav pushes it toward mid on.
Tosses it up now, inviting the bog shot, Yadav mistimes the heave toward extra cover.
FOUR! Slapped away! Short and outside off, Umesh Yadav rocks back and cuts it past point for a boundary. The 300 is now up for India.
Nicely flighted, on a nagging length and around middle, just turning away a touch. Yadav manages to keep it out.
Tossed up, around off and this is defended off the front foot.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone for the keeper to collect.
On a good length around off, this is tapped away toward point.
FOUR! Banged in short and over middle, Jaydev Unadkat gets on top of the bounce and pulls it away into the square leg fence for a boundary.
Just not finding his rhythm yet Taskin. This is a length ball pushed well outside the off stump and edging on being called a wide. Nurul Hasan though makes a good diving stop to his right.
Fuller and well outside off again, Unadkat isn't going to play at that one.
Taskin Ahmed comes back in to share the new ball with his skipper. This is full and outside off, just seaming away a touch. Jaydev Unadkat leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery, on off stump, Umesh Yadav solidly keeps it out off the front foot.
Drops it a bit short and on off, Jaydev Unadkat punches it toward cover for a run.
Tossed up, full and on leg stump, Yadav heaves it down to long on for a single.

FOUR! Streaky but India won't mind. Quicker one, angled into middle, Umesh Yadav looks to block but there's a big gap between bat and pad. The ball takes the inside edge and goes past the leg stump and into the fine leg fence.
Tossed up around off, Umesh Yadav blocks it out.
Umesh Yadav walks in.

OUT! LBW! The skipper has done the job for his team and India lose their eighth. This is flatter and angled into middle and leg. Ashwin looks to come forward and block but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a loud appeal and Shakib Al Hasan strikes straightaway with the new ball as Ravichandran Ashwin has been deemed lbw. Ashwin does review it though. UltraEdge is checked first and there's no spike on it. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is clipping leg stump and Ashwin has to walk back. That wicket was also Shakib's 650th wicket in all of international cricket!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: The second new ball is now available. Will Shakib Al Hasan take it right away? Yes, he does and will take it himself.
Fuller and quicker too, Jaydev Unadkat blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on off turning it away from the right-hander, Jaydev Unadkat punches it to point for a brace.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Jaydev Unadkat defends it to short covers.
This one lands on off, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it to long off for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to short covers.
Slightly shorter one, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to the man at mid on.
This was similar to the last delivery, Jaydev Unadkat again blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on off, Jaydev Unadkat lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Jaydev Unadkat cuts it but finds the fielder at point.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid off.
Bowls it fuller again, Jaydev Unadkat moves forward to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Dot.
Full on the stumps. Unadkat defends it to short covers.

Fuller and on the middle with a sharp turn away from the batter, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to defend it but misses. Taijul Islam thinks that there was a slight edge and Shakib Al Hasan decides to go upstairs. Replay shows that there was no bat involved and the onfield decision stands.
Fuller on the stumps as Ashwin defends it back to the bowler.
Bowls it fuller again, Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to extra covers. Dot.
Fuller length around off, Ashwin drives it to the diving cover fielder.
Fuller one with some turn, Jaydev Unadkat looks to block it but miscues it to mid-wicket. They cross.
Goes fuller and on off, Jaydev Unadkat lunges and blocks it away.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and defends it away.

FOUR! Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin moves forward and lofts it over mid on for a boundary! He brings up 3000 runs in Test cricket and becomes the second-fastest player to 400 wickets and 3000 runs behind Sir Richard Hadlee.

Nicely tossed up by Shakib Al Hasan as he sees Ravichandran Ashwin coming down the track and this one is angled into middle stump. Ashwin looks to block but fails to get his front leg out of the way and there is a huge shout by the Bangladeshi players for lbw. It is turned down and Shakib reviews it immediately. Nothing on UltraEdge and everything seems fine on Ball Tracking as well but the impact is more than 3 meters in front of the stumps and hence it cannot be given out. Ashwin survives!
Short and wide, Ashwin cuts it away to the diving point fielder.
Quicker one on leg, Ashwin looks to play at it but gets his pads as the ball lobs to the man at short leg who drops it.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Ashwin defends it with soft hands.
Tosses it up on off, Unadkat lunges and blocks it away.
Quicker one outside off, Unadkat looks to defend it but misses.
Another one outside off, Ashwin knocks it to covers for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Ashwin taps it to the man at covers.
Another fuller one, Ashwin lunges and defends it to mid off.
Bowls it on off, this is defended out solidly.
FOUR! Nice shot. Fuller and on middle, Unadkat gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Bowls it fuller and keeps a tad low, Unadkat defends it again.
Fuller one again, Unadkat lunges and blocks it away.
Outside off this time, Unadkat let's it through towards the keeper.
Fuller and on off, Unadkat defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside leg, Unadkat leaves it alone.

Drinks! With Shreyas Iyer and Rishabh Pant going great guns, Bangladesh seemed likely to concede a big first-innings lead. This might not be the case as the Bangladeshi spinners have turned the game on its head. Shakib Al Hasan has made smart bowling changes and both set batters are now back in the hut. India already have a 46-run lead and would want to stretch it beyond the 100-run mark. A fascinating and important final phase of play on Day 2 awaits.
Bowls it on middle with some turn, Unadkat guides it to backward point for a single.
Fuller and on off, Ashwin drives it to deep covers for one.
This one lands on middle, Ashwin taps it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it on off, Ashwin defends it to mid off again.
Another fuller ball, Ashwin eases it to mid off.
Short and wide, Ashwin cuts it away to the diving point fielder.
Bowls it outside off, Jaydev Unadkat taps it to covers again.
Fuller and on off, Jaydev Unadkat defends it to short covers.
Jaydev Unadkat isthe new man in.

OUT! PLUMB! Fuller and on off with a hint of turn, Shreyas Iyer looks to sweep it away but misses and the ball hits his thigh. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Shreyas Iyer decides to go upstairs. Fair delivery and Ultra Edge shows a flat line. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Shreyas Iyer has to walk out. He departs for 87!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Iyer eases it to covers and scampers through for a single. There was a midfield from the fielder. If he had been quick to grab the ball this would have been close!
Bowls it on off, Iyer drives it to covers for a single.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the man at point.
This one lands on off, Ashwin defends it to silly point.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Fuller and on off, Ashwin flicks it using his wrists through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Slightly shorter and outside off, Iyer punches it to covers for one.
Bowls it on off, Iyer eases it to the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands down middle and leg, Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it on off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it to the man at silly point.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to the man at mid on.
Ravichandran Ashwin is the new man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Axar goes for the big one as he gets the height and not the distance. This is fuller and on off, Axar Patel lofts it over mid off. The ball goes in the air near the ropes and Najmul Hossain Shanto takes a good catch over his head and just stops before the ropes. They check the replay if he has touched the fence, and it shows he hasn't. The big screen shows OUT and Axar Patel makes his way back into the hut.
Commentary.Howout: c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller again, on off. Shreyas Iyer moves forward and knocks it to extra covers for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on leg, Shreyas Iyer gets on his knees and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary!
Floated up on middle, Axar Patel pushes it toward mid on.
Flighted and on the pads, Axar nudges it towards leg gully.
EDGED AND FOUR! This is flatter and around off stump, Axar Patel rocks back to cut but gets a thick outside edge that runs away into the third man fence.
This is pushed through fuller and around middle, Axar Patel pushes at it with hard hands and past the man at silly point.
Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Iyer leans on and eases it through cover-point for one.
Very full and on off stump, Shreyas Iyer keeps it out on the leg side.
Quicker one, outside off and left alone for the keeper to collect.
Length ball on the pads, flicked away towards square leg.

Half an appeal from the fielders but the umpire isn't interested. This is angling into the pads, Axar goes deep in his crease and nudges it in front of short leg who throws the ball onto the stumps and appeals for a run out.
Floated full and outside off, Axar Patel drives it straight toward extra cover.
Tossed up full and on middle, flicked away toward mid-wicket.
This is slower and shorter around middle, Shreyas Iyer works it off the back foot through mid-wicket for one.
A wicket-maiden! This is fired in on off stump, Axar Patel pushes it out on the off side.
Axar Patel walks in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Rishabh Pant departs in the nervous 90s for the sixth time in his Test career and the crowd is absolutely elated. Mehidy Hasan goes a bit wider of the crease and floats it up on a nagging length around the off pole. The ball does turn away a bit but Pant goes on the back foot instead of coming forward and looks to have a dab at it. The ball deflects off the outside edge and goes into Nurul Hasan's gloves. Pant departs after yet another game-changing knock and India now lead by 26 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Nicely drifted into the pads this time, Pant blocks it off the front foot.
Drifted onto middle and leg, Pant defends it out.
Tosses it up now, full and around middle, Pant plays it with soft hands toward backward point.
Floated, full and outside off, left alone by Pant.
Nicely flighted, on middle and leg, Iyer blocks it out.
Keeps it around off, Pant is able to push it away onto the off side of a single.
Nicely flighted, fuller and wide of the off stump. Rishabh Pant looks to get a big stride across and block but is beaten once again.
On the pads, Pant tucks it toward backward square leg.
Tossed up, on a nagging length and around off, Pant looks to block but is beaten past the outside edge.
Shakib starts off with a flighted delivery outside off, Pant watches it closely and leaves it alone.
FOUR! Sweetly timed! A tad shorter and around middle, Shreyas Iyer waits for it and pushes it back past the bowler for a boundary.
Shorter and around off, played off the back foot onto the off side for one more.
Tossed up on middle, this is eased away through covers for one.
Beaten! Tossed up on a shorter length and around off, Iyer looks to play it off the back foot but is well beaten.

Close but not close enough for Bangladesh! This is flatter around off, keeping a tad low. Shreyas Iyer punches it off the back foot toward extra cover where the fielder makes half a stop. The batters look for the quick single but the fielder from mid off is quick to latch onto it. Pant is sent back and the bowler does whip off the bails. The replays show that Pant dived in well and made his ground.
Floated up, full and around middle, this is flicked away straight to square leg.
Slight halt! Rishabh Pant is feeling a bit uneasy and the physio is out to have a check. He looks fine now and we are good to go.
This is short and outside off, Iyer pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Banged in halfway down the track and down leg as well. Shreyas Iyer leaves it alone and Khaled Ahmed has a bit of a chat with him. Iyer grins and frustrates the bowler further.
A sharp bouncer now, on the money. This is bowled around leg stump and angling across the helmet of the batter. Iyer sways away from the line of the ball.
Goes back to bowling it short and around leg stump, Iyer fails to get it away.

FOUR! Much better from Khaled but still the ball ends up in the ropes. Goes full and angles it just across off, Shreyas Iyer is late on the drive but gets it through the vacant mid off region. The ball trickles away into the fence and the 150-run stand is up between these two.
Banged in short and well down the leg side, Iyer doesn't play at it.
Shortish length around leg stump, Iyer swivels and tucks it down to deep backward square leg for another easy single.
Pitched up around middle, this is driven firmly but straight to mid on.
Slower one, pitched up on middle and leg, Pant flicks it through mid-wicket and turns the strike over.
Switches to around the wicket and bowls a bumper over leg stump, Iyer is able to get inside the line and play a controlled pull shot down to fine leg for one.
FOUR! A rank half-volley outside off, Shreyas Iyer stands tall and thumps it uppishly through extra cover for a boundary. Bangladesh currently seem to have no answer to this hitting.
Length ball, a touch fuller and angling into off stump, Iyer watchfully keeps it out.
FOUR! Short again and around off, sits up nicely for the batter. Rishabh Pant rocks back and muscles it in front of mid-wicket for a boundary. He moves into the 90s now.
Comes from around the wicket now and bangs it in halfway down the track, flying over Pant's head. The short ball tactic isn't coming off for Khaled Ahmed.
Keeps on banging it in short and on the body, Iyer pulls it down to deep backward square leg for a single.
A good bumper now, over middle and Shreyas Iyer just lets it through to the keeper.
Another one begging to be hit but Shreyas Iyer fails to put it away. This is dragged down over middle, sitting up nicely for the batter but it is hit straight to square leg.
Khaled digs it in short first up and at the body, there to be hit but Iyer mistimes it badly toward square leg.
Khaled Ahmed to bowl from the other end.
A bit of an uneven bounce here. On a good length, bowled from around the stumps and on off stump, Pant looks to block off the front foot but gets a bit taken aback by the extra bounce.
Back of a length and close to the off pole, Iyer allows the ball to come to him before punching it away to deep point for a run.
Staying low! Banged in on a hard length and around off, Iyer looks to pull but the ball stays low and goes under the willow, dying on its way to the keeper.
Fullish length outside off, driven straight to the man at extra cover.
Pushed away and India are now in the lead by 1 run! Pitched up around off, Iyer presses forward and strokes it through the cover region for a couple of runs.
On a hard length and angling into the off pole, Shreyas Iyer gets behind the line of the ball to make the block.

We are back for the final session of Day 2. The umpires and the players have made their way out in the middle. Rishabh Pant and Shreyas Iyer will resume their innings for India. The latter is on strike as Taskin Ahmed will bowl him the first ball after Tea. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

Right then, India are all but about to have a lead in the game, courtesy of this Pant-Iyer partnership. They will be hoping to increase the lead as much as possible whilst Bangladesh will be hoping to restrict them and bundle them as soon as they can. Which side will dominate the final session of Day 2? To find out, join us at 2.00 pm IST (8.30 am GMT) for the final session.

Bangladesh bowlers have struggled in the second session after dominating the first. Taijul Islam bagged three wickets in the first session but hardly managed to trouble the Indian batters in the second session. Taskin Ahmed got the dangerous Virat Kohli out early but none of the bowlers could manage to break this Pant-Iyer partnership. They did get close to getting them on multiple occasions but missed the final touch. They will be hoping to start the final session on a positive note and bag some early wickets and restrict their opponents to a total of around 300 runs.

A session that belonged to India and they are the ones who are in the driver's seat now. After Virat Kohli's early dismissal in the second session, Rishabh Pant and Shreyas Iyer took on the bowling and put up a gritty stand for the team. They have built up a 132 runs partnership and India now trails by only a run. Rishabh Pant is playing on 86 whilst Shreyas Iyer is on 58. India will be hoping that these two continue in the same form and give a good lead by putting up a mammoth total on the scoreboard.
Back of a length, over middle and Pant just defends it down toward silly point. A dot to end and that will be Tea on Day 2!
An attempted bumper around middle and off, Pant just bends his back a bit and leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Back to over the wicket now and serves a length ball on leg stump. Rishabh Pant defends it out.
Through the fielder! Another short ball around leg stump, Shreyas Iyer gets on top of the bounce and pulls it firmly toward square leg where Mominul Haque misfields and allows the single to be taken.
Banged in short and over middle and leg, this is pulled away straight to mid-wicket.
Khaled comes from around the wicket and keeps bowling it short and at the body. Iyer shuffles a bit and tucks it to square leg.
A tad shorter and on leg stump, this is worked away down to wide long on for a single.
SIX! Picks up the length early and dispatches it. This is dragged down by Shakib on off stump, Shreyas Iyer rocks back and pulls it all the way over the cow corner fence for a maximum.
Flighted delivery, on a length and outside off, Iyer eases it to short extra cover.
Tossed up around middle, Shreyas Iyer blocks it off the front foot.
Well bowled! Slows it up a touch and drifts it onto middle, the ball turns away after pitching but Iyer is able to watchfully keep it out.
Shakib Al Hasan brings himself back into the attack and tosses it up full and outside off. Rishabh Pant looks to fetch and sweep but miscues it through mid-wicket. Pant will get the single though.
Shorter in length and on the body, Pant plays a controlled pull shot through backward square leg and picks up a single.
Another short ball down the leg side, Pant ducks under it with ease.
A good bumper, over middle and Rishabh Pant just lets it through to the keeper.

That will be FIFTY for Shreyas Iyer, his 2nd one against Bangladesh. Shorter, bowled from around the stumps and around leg stump. Iyer pulls it down to fine leg for a single. India now trail by just 11 runs.
Banged in short and over middle, Shreyas Iyer with a cracking pull shot but finds the man at square leg.
Starts off with a shortish ball around leg stump, Iyer works it off his hips toward backward square leg.
Khaled Ahmed is brought back into the attack.
SIX! What a shot. Pant you beauty! Fuller and on off, Pant moves forward and lofts it with one hand over long on for a maximum! That has travelled beyond a 100 meters, unreal!
Slightly shorter and on off, Iyer flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, this is defended out solidly.
Fuller and on off, Iyer lunges and blocks it away.
SIX! Bowls it fuller and on off, Iyer dances down the track and lofts it over wide long on for a maximum!
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it to covers.
SIX! Fuller and on off, Pant shimmies down the wicket and heaves it over the long on fence for a maximum! 200 up for India now!
FOUR! Tossed up on leg stump, Rishabh Pant dances down the track and whips it over the leaping man at wide mid on for a boundary.! The 100-run stand is up between this duo now.
Slightly shorter and slower, Iyer works it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it on off, Iyer eases it to mid-wicket.
Fuller again, Iyer lunges and blocks it away.
Fuller and slower on middle, Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Pant steers it to the man at covers. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and slower, down leg. Pant looks to defend it but gets a rap on his pads. A stifled appeal turned down.
Goes fuller and on off, Iyer knocks it to long on for a single.
This one lands on off, Iyer taps it to the man at covers.
Another fuller one as Iyer drives it firmly back towards the bowler who gets a hand on it before the ball goes on to hit the stumps at the bowler's end.
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Mehidy Hasan comes back in to replace Taskin Ahmed.
Keeps it bowling fuller, Pant flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Another fuller one as this is played towards covers for a single.
Fuller and slower one, Iyer taps it to the man at mid off.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter and on off, Iyer hangs back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Pant taps it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Pant gently flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
This one lands outside off, Iyer drives it to covers for two more. Good running!
Bowls it fuller and on off, Iyer knocks it to point for a couple more.
Shorter and on off, Iyer pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
This one lands on off as well, Iyer pushes it uppishly to the man at mid on.
Bowls it on off, Pant steers it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Pant looks to flick it but gets a leading edge towards covers. The ball carries and just falls short of the player. Close!
Another fuller one as this is defended towards the man at covers.
Fuller and on off, Pant eases it to the man at mid on.
Shorter and on off, Pant pushes it to covers for one.

SIX! Bowls it slower again, Pant moves forward and heaves it over long on for a maximum. The fielder there, Mushfiqur Rahim makes an excellent attempt at the fence diving behind but just manages to get his hand to it. Good attempt but if he was on the ropes, it would have been a simple chance.
Fuller and slower on off, Pant blocks it to mid off.
Tosses it up giving it some air, Pant blocks it back towards the bowler.
Mehidy Hasan (11-1-29-0) is back on the field and back into the attack as well.
Bowls it outside off with some extra bounce, Iyer looks to drive it but misses.
Bowls it full and outside off, Pant taps it to point and scampers through for a single.
Fuller and on off, Pant drives it but finds the man at covers.
Wide! Bangs a bouncer on off, Pant lets it through towards the keeper. Wided.
Good length shaping it away from outside off, Pant shoulders arms at it.
On a length and on middle and leg, Pant defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Good length angling it away with some extra bounce, Pant leaves it alone.
Flatter and on middle, Pant sweeps it to square leg for one. He keeps his strike for the next over.
Bowls it full and on off, Pant blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands down leg, Pant defends it with his pads.
SIX! A one handed maximum! Fuller and on off, Pant shimmies down the wicket and lofts it with one hand over long off for a maximum!
Touch shorter and on off, Pant defends it solidly.
Flatter and outside leg, Pant looks to slog it but misses.
Nagging length around off and nipping back in off the deck, Shreyas Iyer looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Drop and run! On a hard length and angled into middle, Pant hangs back and just bunts it in front of silly point for a quick single.
Good length outside off, Pant waits for it and plays it with an angled bat down towards gully.
On a length and angling into the off stump, Pant eases it toward mid on.
Goes fuller now and keeps it around the off stump, Rishabh Pant tentatively keeps it out.
Good length, around the top of off, Pant defends it back on the deck. Pant has a chat with the umpire and gets a new pair of gloves out for himself.

Drinks! The game looks good so far and Bangladesh had done well to claw their way up in the game as Taskin Ahmed got rid of Virat Kohli but they have lost all the momentum now. They will hope to bag some quick wickets now and put pressure on the visitors. India will hope that Rishabh Pant and Shreyas Iyer both continue on their merry way and keep counter-attacking as they still trail by 67 runs.
FOUR! Thumped! Tossed up on off stump, Shreyas Iyer advances and this time he just hammers it right back over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Floated up around off, Iyer pushes it out on the off side.
FOUR! Nicely played! On the shorter side and turning it away from off stump, Iyer waits on the back foot and cuts it late into the backward point fence.
Flighted delivery around off, Iyer keeps it out.
